description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a&lt;strong&gt;Head of Care&lt;/strong&gt;with a passion for delivering the best quality of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working 40 hours per week with an on call rota basis, at Cygnet Nield House.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cygnet Nield House in Crewe is our new 30-bed mental health hospital for women. This service will provide a robust personcentred programme of care for women presenting with high risk needs and who may demonstrate difficulties with engagement or motivation with therapeutic programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day-to-Day...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide leadership, direction and supervision to all clinical and support staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and evaluate agreed systems of clinical and operational support aimed at the continual professional development of the Nursing Team and delivery of a high level of care to our clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide effective communication to both the care team and Multi-Disciplinary Team, acting as a positive role model at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS and employee discount scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% NMC registration renewal paid by Cygnet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RCNi membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bespoke career pathways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible shift patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plus many more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the effective admission/discharge of allclients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Registered Mental Nurse (RMN) with a current pin number&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently operating as a Ward manager / Head of Care or significant experience in a Senior Nursing role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working as part of a multidisciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of providing clinical and managerial supervision, offering support in making clear and consistent clinical decisions along with the ability to lead and motivate a Nursing team effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Ability to deputise in a Clinical Manager role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Desirable:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in leadership, research and assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have up to date knowledge of legislation in relation to mental health / personality disorder and co-morbid disordered eating.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have leadership and management training or qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum oftwo years post qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Health Care&lt;/strong&gt;has been providing a national network of high quality specialist mental health services for 30 years&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Nield House&lt;/strong&gt;will be split into two distinct wards, each offering specialist mental health services:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clarion Ward,&lt;/strong&gt;a 15 bed highly specialised service for women with a personality disorder and co-morbid disordered eating.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compton Ward,&lt;/strong&gt;a 15 bed acute service for women. The service will provide a safe and stabilising environment for women who are experiencing an acute episode of mental illness and require an emergency admission.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What next?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you care about making a difference – we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Click the link to apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
